en_272870_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – Train operations along the main railway line have been restored.
en_272870_1	The train operation from Rambukkana to Moratuwa was forced to stop between the Ambepussa and Bothale train stations at around 05:45 a.m. today (June 1) as a body was discovered on the tracks.
en_272870_2	Personnel at Ambepussa train station has informed Police of the matter.
en_272870_3	Seven trains including one that was proceeding to Moratuwa was forced to stop until Police arrived at the location.
en_272870_4	A tense situation arose when passengers voiced their protest at the delay.
en_272870_5	Following the arrival of Police, the remains were removed from the tracks and taken to the morgue at Wathupitiwala Hospital.
en_272870_6	Police suspect the individual could have been knocked down by another train and died thereafter The trains which were forced to stop for almost two hours were finally allowed to proceed at 07:35 a.m.
